## Executive Summary

MosaikWeb is an e-commerce platform built on a solid Next.js 15 foundation with Clerk authentication, Drizzle ORM (PostgreSQL/Supabase), and well-structured server actions. The codebase demonstrates **above-average security consciousness** — Content Security Policy headers, XSS sanitization, rate limiting, audit logging, file upload validation, and RBAC via Clerk session claims are all in place.

However, this audit identified **2 Critical**, **5 High**, **7 Medium**, and **6 Low** severity findings across the six evaluation dimensions. The most urgent flaws are **exposed production secrets in the [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/.env.local) file visible to the AI agent** (and potentially committed to version control) and the **admin store cookie lacking security flags**.

---

## 1. Security & Privacy

### 🔴 FLAW SEC-01: Production Secrets Exposed in [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/.env.local)

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Risk Level** | 🔴 **CRITICAL** |
| **Location** | [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/.env.local) |
| **The Flaw** | The [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/.env.local) file contains **real production credentials** in plaintext: a Supabase connection string with a real password (`55n3N%40CP%26mSMwjW`), Clerk API keys (`sk_test_...`), a Supabase service role JWT, and a Resend API key. While `.env*` is in [.gitignore](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/.gitignore), these credentials are visible to any process/tool with filesystem access. |
| **The "Why"** | If this file is ever accidentally committed, leaked via a CI pipeline log, or otherwise exposed, an attacker gains **full database admin access**, **Supabase service-role bypass** (bypasses RLS), **Clerk tenant admin access**, and **ability to send emails** impersonating the business. Worst-case: full data exfiltration, account takeover, database destruction, and financial fraud. |
| **Recommendation** | **Immediately rotate all keys.** 1) Generate new Supabase, Clerk, and Resend credentials. 2) Verify [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/.env.local) is not in any Git history (`git log --all --full-history -- .env.local`). If it is, use `git filter-branch` or BFG Repo Cleaner to purge it. 3) Use a secrets manager (e.g., Vercel env vars, Doppler, or Vault) in production. 4) Add a pre-commit hook that scans for secrets (e.g., `gitleaks`). |

