## 2. Development Practices & Code Quality

### 🟡 FLAW DEV-01: `as any` Type Overrides in CategoriesAdminClient

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Risk Level** | 🟡 **MEDIUM** |
| **Location** | [components/CategoriesAdminClient.tsx:62, 159, 250](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/components/CategoriesAdminClient.tsx) |
| **The Flaw** | Three instances of `as any` type casting found: [(cat as any).storeType](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/lib/utils.ts#4-7) and event handler casting. This bypasses TypeScript's type system. |
| **The "Why"** | TypeScript strict mode is enabled (good!), but `as any` defeats its purpose. If the [ProductCategory](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/db/schema.ts#256-257) type changes or `storeType` is ever removed/renamed, these lines will silently break instead of throwing compile errors. |
| **Recommendation** | 1) Ensure the [ProductCategory](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/db/schema.ts#256-257) type exported from schema includes `storeType`. 2) Replace [(cat as any).storeType](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/lib/utils.ts#4-7) with `cat.storeType`. 3) Use proper typing: `onChange={(e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLSelectElement>) => setFormStoreType(e.target.value as "streetwear" | "formal" | "both")}`. |

---

### 🟡 FLAW DEV-02: Bloated Component Files

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Risk Level** | 🟡 **MEDIUM** |
| **Location** | [components/ProductDetailClient.tsx](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/components/ProductDetailClient.tsx) (32KB, ~800+ lines), [components/EditProductForm.tsx](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/components/EditProductForm.tsx) (18KB), [components/CreateProductForm.tsx](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/components/CreateProductForm.tsx) (15KB), [components/Navbar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/components/Navbar.tsx) (13KB) |
| **The Flaw** | Several component files exceed 400 lines, with [ProductDetailClient.tsx](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/components/ProductDetailClient.tsx) at 32KB. These files likely mix business logic, state management, and UI presentation. |
| **The "Why"** | Large monolithic components are harder to test, debug, and maintain. They also hurt tree-shaking and code-splitting. A bug in one section can have cascading effects throughout the entire file. |
| **Recommendation** | Break large components into: 1) **Custom hooks** for business logic (e.g., `useProductDetail`, `useProductForm`). 2) **Subcomponents** for UI sections (e.g., `ProductImageGallery`, `ProductSizeSelector`, `ProductPriceDisplay`). 3) Keep each file under 300 lines as a guideline. |

