### 🟡 FLAW DEV-03: Duplicated Upload Logic

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Risk Level** | 🟡 **MEDIUM** |
| **Location** | [lib/uploadImages.ts](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/lib/uploadImages.ts) — 4 nearly identical upload functions (lines 13-55, 63-104, 112-153, 161-202) |
| **The Flaw** | [uploadProductImage](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/lib/uploadImages.ts#8-56), [uploadHeroImage](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/lib/uploadImages.ts#59-105), [uploadHomeVideo](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/lib/uploadImages.ts#108-154), and [uploadLookImage](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/lib/uploadImages.ts#157-203) share ~90% identical code, differing only by storage path and file kind. |
| **The "Why"** | DRY violation. If you need to change the upload logic (e.g., add virus scanning, change fallback behavior, fix a bug), you must update 4 places. This is error-prone and has already led to subtly different error messages. |
| **Recommendation** | Refactor into a single generic upload function: ```typescript
async function uploadFile(
  file: File,
  filename: string,
  kind: "image" | "video",
  storagePath: string
): Promise<{ url: string; error?: string }>
```
Then each specific function becomes a one-liner wrapper. |

