### 🟢 FLAW DEV-04: FormData `as string` Casts Without Null Checks

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Risk Level** | 🟢 **LOW** |
| **Location** | [actions/createProduct.ts:20-26](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/createProduct.ts#L20-L26), [actions/categories.ts:92-99](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/categories.ts#L92-L99), others |
| **The Flaw** | `formData.get("name") as string` is used throughout actions. `FormData.get()` can return `null`, but `as string` suppresses the TypeScript error without handling the null case. |
| **The "Why"** | If a form field is missing or renamed, `as string` silently passes `null` as `"null"` (string) through the pipeline, potentially creating products with name `"null"`. The subsequent `.trim()` calls would succeed on the string `"null"`. |
| **Recommendation** | Use a helper function or Zod `formData` parsing: ```typescript
const name = z.string().min(1).parse(formData.get("name"));
``` Or use `formData.get("name")?.toString()` with explicit null checking. |

