### 🟢 FLAW DEV-05: Missing Return Types on Several Server Actions

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Risk Level** | 🟢 **LOW** |
| **Location** | [actions/hero.ts:11](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/hero.ts#L11) ([getHeroImages](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/hero.ts#11-22)), [actions/hero.ts:24](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/hero.ts#L24) ([getAllHeroImages](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/hero.ts#23-35)), [actions/hero.ts:36](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/hero.ts#L36) ([addHeroImage](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/hero.ts#36-53)), [actions/hero.ts:54](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/hero.ts#L54) ([deleteHeroImage](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/hero.ts#54-63)), and similar in [lookbook.ts](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/lookbook.ts), [video.ts](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/actions/video.ts) |
| **The Flaw** | Many exported functions lack explicit return type annotations, relying on TypeScript inference. |
| **The "Why"** | Without explicit return types, a refactor could silently change the API contract. The consumer gets `any` if inference fails or the server action return type is complex. This makes the codebase harder to navigate and reason about. |
| **Recommendation** | Add explicit return types to all exported server actions: ```typescript
export async function getHeroImages(storeType?: string): Promise<HeroImage[]> {
``` |

