## 4. Usability & UX (Accessibility)

### 🟡 FLAW UX-01: Missing ARIA Labels and Semantic HTML

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Risk Level** | 🟡 **MEDIUM** |
| **Location** | [app/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/app/page.tsx), [app/[storeType]/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/app/%5BstoreType%5D/page.tsx) |
| **The Flaw** | 1) The root page split-screen uses `<Link>` elements as large click areas but lacks `aria-label` attributes. 2) The store home page has multiple `<section>` elements without `aria-labelledby` or `aria-label`. 3) The hero fallback image has `alt=""` (empty string). 4) Social media links in the footer use `href="#"` with no `aria-label`. |
| **The "Why"** | Screen readers can't convey the purpose of these interactive areas. Users navigating with assistive technology won't understand the page structure. WCAG 2.1 Level A compliance requires meaningful link text and image alternatives. |
| **Recommendation** | 1) Add `aria-label="Enter Streetwear Store"` to the left Link, similar for Formal. 2) Add `aria-label` to each `<section>` (e.g., `aria-label="Shop categories"`). 3) Give the fallback hero a meaningful alt text or use `role="presentation"`. 4) Replace `href="#"` with actual URLs and add `aria-label="Follow us on Instagram"`. |

---

### 🟢 FLAW UX-02: Payment Method Select Uses Raw `<select>` Without Accessibility Styling

| Attribute | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Risk Level** | 🟢 **LOW** |
| **Location** | [components/CheckoutForm.tsx:174-183](file:///c:/Users/PC%20FACTORY/Desktop/MosaikWeb/components/CheckoutForm.tsx#L174-L183) |
| **The Flaw** | The payment method uses a raw `<select>` element with custom Tailwind classes instead of the project's UI `Select` component from Shadcn/Radix. Also, the CARD and BANK_TRANSFER options are listed but there's no payment processing logic for them — only COD appears functional. |
| **The "Why"** | Inconsistent component usage affects maintainability and UX consistency. Offering non-functional payment options is misleading to users. |
| **Recommendation** | 1) Use the Shadcn `Select` component for consistency. 2) Either implement Card/Bank Transfer processing or remove those options until they're functional. Add a note like "More payment options coming soon." |

